<br>
     As I fellow cleric I must charge you with malpractice. You must learn to use the F keys. In many crowded areas where the action is fast and furious the mouse will defintely lag out. Many time my mouse cursor seems to disappear in a dungeon. The only patients I have lost are either when I ran out of mana or when the lag is so bad that the heal hits but they were already dead even though their health bar said otherwise.<br>
<br>
Lexxi<br>
19th Prayer<br>
Cleric of Brell<br>
Ak'Anon<br>
<br>
PS. also use the assist key, only use the mouse when rooted a mob out of the way, and if F8 does not target them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaeonii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeonii</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/1/01 12:02:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the mouse doesn't work...</span><hr size=1> Lexxi,<br>
<br>
Thanks for replying to both my posts - here and in the polls.  Heh heh - I said I've been a cleric three times.  But I've never been one past level 19, so I've not really dealt with the lag I so oft hear tell about from those level 30+ dungeon dwellers.<br>
<br>
You are my inspiration.  Perhaps I will try to give those F keys a go, after all.  Perhaps I can convince some of my group to practice with me in a noob garden, so I can get the feel for this someplace where we're not going to die while I &quot;practice&quot; medicine.<br>
<br>
I've just been very afraid that I will forget who is what number when it really matters most.  But practice makes perfect, and hopefully, my liscense for practicing won't get revoked.<br>
<br>
Thanks again for your replies, as I have not really had opportunities to learn from others of my profession.  Your insight is helpful : )<br>
<br>
Æonii <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urestoriacondition.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Restoria Condition</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/1/01 3:03:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the mouse doesn't work...</span><hr size=1> I too have a habit of using the &quot;party box&quot; to target my group members, but i have all my heal spells tied to hotkeys that tell my group what spell I am casting on who and casts it at the same time, so i merely have to press my number that corresponds to that hotkey instead of then moving my mouse from the party box, across the screen to the gem area where the spells are located.  <br>
<br>
(Its late, sorry if that made little sense.)<br>
<br>
Example: The enchanter is getting beat on by a mob he was trying to mez.  <br>
Use mouse to click on that member in my party box, then hit the number 6 which says I am healing that person and casts the spell. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Maybe that will help when in the heat of battle habit makes you have your mouse in hand.<br>
<br>
In addition, I almost never have my spell effects on.  Sure it looks nice, but with a lot of actionh its just too much for lag.<br>
<br>
~Restoria Fallenheart<br>
Human Vicar of Karana's Teachings<br>
Medical Staff of Fire and Fury<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaeonii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeonii</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/1/01 8:55:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the mouse doesn't work...</span><hr size=1> Restoria,<br>
<br>
Love that name, by the way...<br>
<br>
Two great minds think alike!  The sad shame is that I was telling my party members that I was healing the Froglok because that hotkey (along with Light Healing) is one of the few that I actually tell peeps what I am doing, because it's what I do most.<br>
<br>
I have my two heal hotkeys at the very top of my hotkey bank on the left.  I have my target box right above that, and my party box right above that. I adjust the height of my party box behind the target box to match the number of people in my party, so as to always keep members as close to my heal keys as possible.<br>
<br>
I move my gem box behind the Ability/Skill/Social buttons on the right (I have a small screen and need all the room I can get), and only pull it out to change spells.<br>
<br>
I just wasn't reading my own messages because it was such an intense moment while looking at his health bar (and the wiz's also) and my mana bar match speed in dwindling.  It is a hard job to watch the health of many, watch mana, watch text, *and* ward off your own aggro.  But you guys know all about that.<br>
___<br>
<br>
It's the saving that satisfies that calls us to this job, and nothing else matters, even if the job is a hard one.  I've played many other classes, and I keep coming back to clericing, because dwindling health bars hurts my eyes.<br>
<br>
For any non-clerics reading this, don't get the impression that I'm a bad cleric.  Just had a bad night.  And I would love to have the opportunity to party with some other good clerics to learn off of each other.<br>
<br>
/twitch-ack  There I go again.  I've rambled.  No more posts from me for a while.  heh heh...<br>
<br>
Æonii <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uaeonii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeonii</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 12/1/01 9:11:36 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/7/02 7:29:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the mouse doesn't work...</span><hr size=1> Aeonii,<br>
<br>
     Sounds like you are learning fast. If you want a good place to practice, come to Highhold. The pass is good on the orc side until about 20 and then at 21 go to the keep.<br>
     The dungeon in the keep is INTENSE at level 21-23. Since you do not have greater heal yet, you have to learn to use heal and celestial remedy effectively. Also when to use these heals without aggro is very important to. Ahh, you cannot forget your best friend Divine Aura. Use DA after that big fast heal on the tank. Instant anti-aggro.<br>
     Another tip, YOU are the healer, if you have a problem with wwhich F key to use, make everyone regroup with the primary tank the leader and thesecondary tanks joining 2nd. You can then hotkey as such F2-F4 tanks, F5,F6 and you F1 casters, that can help the confusion, I have done this at times. or you can remap your keyboard so the group is F1-F5 and you are F6.<br>
     I will be in the Highkeep dungeon most of this week or until I hit level 24 and get greater healing if you would like to come play!<br>
<br>
Lexxi Ledenyetz<br>
22nd Blessing<br>
Cleric of Brell<br>
Ak'Anon<br>
Spelunking Manager - Ledenyetz Troupe<br>
